Grateful for this 6 year journey🤍

I went through it all… depression, trauma, the crying myself to sleep, multiple heartbreaks, not knowing the woman I wanted to be, lacking self worth, self love, self respect.

When you guys see the 🌻Lily🌻now feeling confident, stepping into the gym without hesitation.. I didn’t magically wake up one day and say “I’m confident now.” It doesn’t work that way. It’s building bricks, one day at a time, taking every bad situation as a learning curve to grow, allowing yourself to forgive, to let go of the bad and look forward to a bright future ✨

The secret to the sauce is : NEVER GIVE UP ON YOURSELF ! Even when life is tearing you down. I can honestly and openly say this … YOUR CURRENT SITUATION, is NOT YOUR PERMANENT SITUATION. Trust me! I felt I was going to be stuck in a toxic place for the rest of my life but nahhh BABY .. God always has a plan. Trust it even if it takes years. 

I hope this helps someone today that you WILL be happy one day and everything is going to be okay. 🫶🏼

WE ARE STARTING OFF THE WEEK STRONG🤎

We are alive, we are breathing and you have the opportunity today to take control of your life and do better! 

This workout can be done at home or the gym. If you have bands, dumbbells you can still have an effective workout and see results. Remain consistent, don’t give up and go put in that work! ✔️ 

All bands from @thexbands @xbandstraining {code: LILY10}

Workout :

#1 superset
*4x15 hip thrusts into 15 banded abductors 

#2
*3x20 kickbacks - make sure back is aligned and straight, don’t dip your back when extending your leg back. Brace your core.

#3
*4x12 step ups. These can be modified. You can do this with a long band, dumbbells or BODYWEIGHT. If you are having a hard time with your balance, you can get near a wall and hold yourself for balance.

#5
*4x15 RDLS - these are perfect to practice “hinging at your hips.” You don’t need to go super slow, stop at your knees or until you feel the stretch in your glutes/hammies. My back is straight, I’m looking down the whole time, and allowing myself to go through the movement. 

#6
*4x10 static lunges 

#7 (finisher 🔥)
*3x30 seconds - single arm DB clean & press (each arm 30 sec)

If you’re a beginner, and some of these movements seem challenging, don’t give up. Keep practicing , keep showing up 🫶🏼

Nutmeg 
Cinnamon
Maple syrup
Brown sugar
Baking soda
Walnuts
Oatmeal

Instructions:
CRUST:
1C almond flour , mix in 2tbsp butter, 1 whole egg, salt
Bake crust for 5 min. Put aside 

Apples:
In a pan melt butter, add in cubed apples, nutmeg, cinnamon , baking soda, brown sugar, maple syrup

Topping:

1. Start with taking walks, learning proper weight lifting form, stay disciplined to 2-3x a week at the gym or home workouts. Once you master that for a month then increase to 4x. This is your journey!

2. NUTRITION!!! This is a big one! Don’t switch your whole entire meal plan and cut out everything cold turkey. Be realistic and honest with yourself. Majority of us are so motivated in the beginning and we are good for 2 weeks then binge eat and fall back into the same cycles of eating. Your body will crave those sweets/burgers/pizza. Instead limit the # of times you eat out. Cut out small things from your diet. Or switch to lower sodium/sugar free sauces/ sparkling drinks instead of regular soda. Once you can do that , cut those drinks out to 1-2x a week. Balance is key here. If you don’t like fish don’t eat it lol, if you having trouble with veggie intake, then eat the veggies you enjoy!

3. RECOVERY🥱- we all avoid this lol but just telling you from experience I’ve injured my back 3x , lumbar sprain and it is NOT fun! If you don’t have time to do it at the gym then do it before bed or in the morning before work! Get your blood flowing and prevent your muscles from being super sore. Especially when you’re first beginning your body will remain sore and you will not want to train. So STRETCH!

4. Motivation comes and goes. We must choose to stay disciplined. This is with work, school, fitness, eating. It’s not just at the gym. We are all busy and have crazy scheduled… BUT YOU WILL PRIORITIZE WHATS IMPORTANT TO YOU! So your health should always be a PRIORITY! Don’t make excuses, get it done ✅ 

5. Last but not least, enjoy the work you are putting into yourself. There will always be someone who is more shredded than you and someone who is just beginning their journey. Don’t look for validation, stay focused. Look forward, stay humble and choose to be happy!

5 mistakes you make when you begin your fitness journey 🦋

And I say this because this is what I did too and I wish I knew sooner🫶🏼

1. OVERTRAINING - I always went super ham because I wanted results so bad. I was always super sore but didn’t care and never listened to my body.

2. WARMING UP (before workout) & COOLING DOWN (after workout) . I would go into the gym and go straight into my workout with no warmup! This can causes injuries. Take a full 15min to get blood flow moving, prepping your body before your weight training. Also, cooling down after is super important too! Take 10 min to stretch out. 

3. REST DAYS - I never would take rest days lol you need to allow 1-2 days to fully recover. Work on mobility/stretching on your off days. Your body will thank you. It’s okay to take a day off ! 

4. Incorrect form - challenging yourself in weight is great but when you jeopardize a new PR over your form, here comes the injuries and back pain! Remember QUALITY OVER QUANTITY! This is your journey DONT compare yourself to what someone next to you is doing! 

5. ONLY DOING CARDIO 🚫 - don’t get stuck only in the cardio section. Strength training is also important. Don’t be nervous to grab some dumbbells! We need the gains too! Cardio will only help you lose all weight but you will not be building muscle and getting stronger!
